{
  "texts": [
    "The flowchart is shown in Fig. 1.",
    "MeasuresStudents are required to report their demographic information, including gender, grade level, and their late sleeping habits.",
    "Regarding late sleeping habits, a cutoff time of 23:00 is adopted, where going to bed later than 23:00 is classified as staying up late, whereas retiring at or before 23:00 is considered as not engaging in late-night activities [28].",
    "Pittsburgh sleep quality indexThis study used the Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index (PSQI) to evaluate sleep quality and daytime dysfunction.",
    "PSQI is a widely used tool that consists of seven components, covering various aspects of subjective sleep quality and daytime dysfunction [29]."
  ]
}